{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01SDnT1iiR8aoN64aFnCWDeS","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→# Story 9-3: Init orchestrator per-stack iteration\n     2→\n     3→## Status: verifying\n     4→\n     5→## Story\n     6→\n     7→As a developer running `codeharness init` on a multi-stack project,\n     8→I want coverage and OTLP to be configured for each detected stack,\n     9→So that all languages get observability and test coverage.\n    10→\n    11→## Acceptance Criteria\n    12→\n    13→- [x] AC1: Given a multi-stack project (nodejs + rust), when `codeharness init` runs, then coverage tools are detected for each stack independently (c8 for nodejs, cargo-tarpaulin for rust) <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n    14→- [x] AC2: Given a multi-stack project (nodejs + rust), when `codeharness init` runs, then OTLP packages are installed for each stack independently (npm packages for nodejs, cargo crates for rust) <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n    15→- [x] AC3: Given a multi-stack project, when `codeharness init` runs, then info messages list all detected stacks (e.g., `Stack detected: Node.js (package.json) + Rust (Cargo.toml)`) <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n    16→- [x] AC4: Given a multi-stack project, when state is created, then `state.stacks` contains all detected stack names and `state.app_type` reflects primary stack <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n    17→\n    18→## Tasks/Subtasks\n    19→\n    20→- [x] Task 1: Update `getStackLabel()` in `docs-scaffold.ts` to accept `string | string[]` and format multi-stack output (e.g., `Node.js (package.json) + Rust (Cargo.toml)`)\n    21→- [x] Task 2: In `init-project.ts` L75, change info message to pass `result.stacks` (or all stack names) to `getStackLabel()` so multi-stack projects show all stacks\n    22→- [x] Task 3: In `init-project.ts` L123, replace single `getCoverageTool(stack)` with per-stack loop over `allStacks`, calling `getCoverageTool()` per stack and storing results (primary stack's tool in `state.coverage.tool` for backward compat)\n    23→- [x] Task 4: In `init-project.ts` L138, replace single `instrumentProject(projectDir, stack, ...)` with per-stack loop over `allStacks`, calling `instrumentProject()` per detection with correct subdirectory path\n    24→- [x] Task 5: Verify `state.stacks` is persisted correctly (already done in story 9-2 at L125 — confirm no changes needed)\n    25→- [x] Task 6: Add test — multi-stack init calls `getCoverageTool()` once per detected stack\n    26→- [x] Task 7: Add test — multi-stack init calls `instrumentProject()` once per detected stack with correct dir\n    27→- [x] Task 8: Add test — info output includes all detected stacks label\n    28→- [x] Task 9: Add test — state file after multi-stack init has `stacks: ['nodejs', 'rust']` and `app_type` set from primary stack\n    29→- [x] Task 10: Add test — single-stack backward compat: single-stack project still works identically\n    30→- [x] Task 11: Run full test suite — verify zero regressions\n    31→\n    32→## Dev Agent Record\n    33→\n    34→### Implementation Plan\n    35→\n    36→- Updated `getStackLabel()` to accept `string | string[] | null` with array support via recursive mapping and `+` join\n    37→- Changed info message to use `result.stacks` array when populated, falling back to single stack\n    38→- Added per-stack coverage detection loop over `allStacks`, keeping primary stack's tool in `state.coverage.tool`\n    39→- Replaced single `instrumentProject()` with per-stack loop using correct subdirectory paths\n    40→- Added `join` import from `node:path` for subdirectory path construction\n    41→- Confirmed `state.stacks` persistence from story 9-2 is intact\n    42→\n    43→### Debug Log\n    44→\n    45→No issues encountered during implementation.\n    46→\n    47→### Completion Notes\n    48→\n    49→All 11 tasks implemented and verified. 5 new multi-stack tests added to init-project.test.ts, 3 new getStackLabel array tests added to docs-scaffold.test.ts. Full test suite: 3105 tests pass across 114 files with zero regressions.\n    50→\n    51→## File List\n    52→\n    53→- `src/modules/infra/init-project.ts` — Per-stack coverage and OTLP loops, multi-stack info message, added `join` import\n    54→- `src/modules/infra/docs-scaffold.ts` — `getStackLabel()` now accepts `string | string[] | null`\n    55→- `src/modules/infra/__tests__/init-project.test.ts` — 6 multi-stack orchestration tests (added OTLP root-dir matching test), updated mocks\n    56→- `src/modules/infra/__tests__/docs-scaffold.test.ts` — 3 new getStackLabel array tests\n    57→- `src/commands/__tests__/init.test.ts` — Updated fail-path tests to mock `detectStacks` instead of removed `detectStack` call\n    58→- `src/lib/state.ts` — Added optional `tools` field to `coverage` interface for per-stack coverage tools map\n    59→\n    60→## Change Log\n    61→\n    62→- 2026-03-23: Implemented per-stack iteration for coverage detection and OTLP instrumentation in init orchestrator. Updated getStackLabel for multi-stack display. Added 8 new tests.\n    63→- 2026-03-23: Code review fixes — H1: per-stack coverage loop now stores tools map in state.coverage.tools instead of discarding results; H2: OTLP primary stack matching uses dir==='.' to avoid wrong detection in multi-nodejs projects; M1: eliminated double filesystem scan by removing detectStack() call and deriving root stack from detectStacks() result; added test for OTLP root-dir matching edge case; fixed integration tests in init.test.ts.\n    64→\n    65→## Senior Developer Review (AI)\n    66→\n    67→**Reviewer:** Code Review Workflow on 2026-03-23\n    68→**Outcome:** Changes Requested -> Fixed\n    69→\n    70→### Issues Found: 2 HIGH, 3 MEDIUM, 2 LOW\n    71→\n    72→#### HIGH (fixed)\n    73→1. **H1: Per-stack coverage loop was dead code** — `getCoverageTool()` called per stack but return value discarded. Fixed: now stores results in `state.coverage.tools` map.\n    74→2. **H2: OTLP primary stack matching by stack name only** — `detection.stack === stack` could match a subdirectory detection instead of root. Fixed: added `detection.dir === '.'` guard.\n    75→\n    76→#### MEDIUM (fixed)\n    77→3. **M1: Double filesystem scan** — `detectStack()` and `detectStacks()` both scan the filesystem. Removed `detectStack()` call; root stack derived from `detectStacks()` result.\n    78→4. **M2: Integration tests used removed API** — `init.test.ts` fail-path tests mocked `detectStack` which is no longer called. Fixed: updated to mock `detectStacks`.\n    79→5. **M3: State type missing `tools` field** — `coverage.tools` assigned in init-project.ts but not declared in `HarnessState` interface. Fixed: added optional `tools?: Record<string, string>` to state type.\n    80→\n    81→#### LOW (not fixed — tech debt)\n    82→6. **L1: No `state.coverage.tools` consumer yet** — The tools map is persisted but no existing code reads it. Future stories should consume it.\n    83→7. **L2: `detectAppType` still uses primary stack only** — In multi-stack projects, app type is computed from the root stack only, not considering secondary stacks.\n    84→\n    85→### Verification\n    86→- 3109 tests pass, 0 failures\n    87→- Coverage: 97.03% overall, all 123 files above 80% per-file floor\n    88→\n    89→## Technical Notes\n    90→\n    91→### Current state after story 9-2\n    92→\n    93→Story 9-2 already added `detectStacks` import and basic `stacks` population in `init-project.ts`:\n    94→- L9: `import { detectStack, detectStacks, detectAppType } from '../../lib/stack-detect.js';`\n    95→- L70-71: `const allStacks = detectStacks(projectDir);` and `result.stacks = [...new Set(allStacks.map(s => s.stack))];`\n    96→- L125: `state.stacks = result.stacks as import('../../lib/stack-detect.js').StackName[];`\n    97→\n    98→What is NOT yet multi-stack:\n    99→- L75: `info(\\`Stack detected: ${getStackLabel(stack)}\\`)` — uses single stack, not all stacks\n   100→- L123: `state.coverage.tool = getCoverageTool(stack);` — single stack coverage only\n   101→- L138: `result.otlp = instrumentProject(projectDir, stack, { json: isJson, appType });` — single stack OTLP only\n   102→\n   103→### Changes to `src/modules/infra/init-project.ts`\n   104→\n   105→**Info message (L74-77):** Replace `getStackLabel(stack)` with `getStackLabel(result.stacks)` (after updating `getStackLabel` to accept arrays). Show all stacks in the detection message.\n   106→\n   107→**Per-stack coverage (L123):** Replace single `getCoverageTool(stack)` with iteration over `allStacks`. For each detection, compute the coverage tool. Store primary stack's tool in `state.coverage.tool` for backward compat. Optionally store a `state.coverage.tools` map for future consumers.\n   108→\n   109→**Per-stack OTLP (L134-139):** Replace single `instrumentProject()` call with loop:\n   110→```ts\n   111→for (const detection of allStacks) {\n   112→  const stackDir = detection.dir === '.' ? projectDir : path.join(projectDir, detection.dir);\n   113→  const stackOtlp = instrumentProject(stackDir, detection.stack, { json: isJson, appType });\n   114→  // Collect results; primary stack's result goes to result.otlp for backward compat\n   115→}\n   116→```\n   117→\n   118→### Important: coverage.ts and otlp.ts internals do NOT change\n   119→\n   120→`getCoverageTool()` and `instrumentProject()` keep their single-stack signatures. The orchestrator loops — the internals don't know about multi-stack. This is the minimal API surface change strategy from the tech spec.\n   121→\n   122→### `getStackLabel()` in docs-scaffold.ts\n   123→\n   124→Currently accepts `string | null`. Needs to also accept `string[]` to format multi-stack labels. When given an array, join with ` + ` separator. The stack-to-label mapping (nodejs -> `Node.js (package.json)`, rust -> `Rust (Cargo.toml)`, python -> `Python`) already exists.\n   125→\n   126→### Test file\n   127→\n   128→Update `src/modules/infra/__tests__/init-project.test.ts`:\n   129→- Mock `detectStacks()` to return multi-stack result `[{ stack: 'nodejs', dir: '.' }, { stack: 'rust', dir: '.' }]`\n   130→- Verify `getCoverageTool()` called once per stack\n   131→- Verify `instrumentProject()` called once per stack with correct dir\n   132→- Verify state has `stacks: ['nodejs', 'rust']`\n   133→- Verify single-stack still works (backward compat)\n   134→\n   135→## Files to Change\n   136→\n   137→- `src/modules/infra/init-project.ts` — Add per-stack iteration loops for coverage detection and OTLP instrumentation, update info message to show all stacks\n   138→- `src/modules/infra/docs-scaffold.ts` — Update `getStackLabel()` to accept `string | string[]` for multi-stack label formatting\n   139→- `src/modules/infra/__tests__/init-project.test.ts` — Add multi-stack orchestration tests (per-stack coverage, per-stack OTLP, state fields, info messages, backward compat)\n   140→"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01Du6Dm3wXgPT4dCoQ6SefyL","session_id":"e8d3a9d7-303a-4d24-9a07-31410ec54173","uuid":"8974b0e0-ef74-45c5-aa17-2db54157144a","timestamp":"2026-03-23T15:13:22.781Z"}
