{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_013Lsr6xeLDGYFoJVKujJzNb","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→---\n     2→stepsCompleted: [1, 2, 3, 4, 5, 6, 7, 8]\n     3→inputDocuments:\n     4→  - prd-operational-excellence.md\n     5→  - architecture-overhaul.md\n     6→  - product-brief-operational-excellence-2026-03-19.md\n     7→workflowType: 'architecture'\n     8→project_name: 'codeharness'\n     9→user_name: 'BMad'\n    10→date: '2026-03-19'\n    11→---\n    12→\n    13→# Architecture Decision Document — Operational Excellence\n    14→\n    15→_Extends the overhaul architecture (architecture-overhaul.md) with observability analysis, audit, and infrastructure validation capabilities._\n    16→\n    17→## Project Context Analysis\n    18→\n    19→### Requirements Overview\n    20→\n    21→28 FRs across 5 capability areas:\n    22→- **Observability Static Analysis (FR1-5):** Source scanning, log coverage, gap detection\n    23→- **Observability Runtime Validation (FR6-9):** Test telemetry verification, gap detection\n    24→- **Observability Coverage Metric (FR10-12):** Metric computation, enforcement, tracking\n    25→- **Audit Command (FR13-21):** Comprehensive compliance check, story generation\n    26→- **Infrastructure Guidelines (FR22-25):** Dockerfile rules, validation, templates\n    27→- **Workflow Enforcement (FR26-28):** Integration with dev/review workflows\n    28→\n    29→### How This Extends the Overhaul Architecture\n    30→\n    31→The overhaul established 5 modules: infra, sprint, verify, dev, review. This sprint adds:\n    32→- **New module: `observability/`** — static analysis, runtime validation, coverage metric\n    33→- **Expanded module: `audit/`** — replaces onboard, uses observability module + existing checks\n    34→- **Extended: `infra/`** — Dockerfile guidelines and validation\n    35→- **Extended: `patches/`** — observability enforcement rules for dev/review\n    36→\n    37→### Technical Constraints\n    38→\n    39→- Existing Result<T> pattern applies to all new functions\n    40→- Module boundary rules from overhaul apply (index.ts exports only, no circular imports)\n    41→- Atomic write pattern for state updates\n    42→- <300 line file limit\n    43→- Must work with both VictoriaMetrics and OpenSearch backends (ObservabilityBackend interface)\n    44→\n    45→### Research Inputs\n    46→\n    47→Technical research (2026-03-19) established:\n    48→- No industry-standard observability coverage metric exists — report static and runtime separately\n    49→- Semgrep is the right static analysis tool — YAML rules, `pattern-not-inside` detects absence of logging\n    50→- Analyzer interface allows tool flexibility — harness cares about gap report format, not which tool produces it\n    51→- Runtime validation matches test coverage paths to telemetry events by module/service, not line-level\n    52→\n    53→## Starter: N/A (Brownfield)\n    54→\n    55→All technology decisions preserved from overhaul architecture. New dependencies: Semgrep (static analysis tool, installed as project dev dependency).\n    56→\n    57→## Core Architectural Decisions\n    58→\n    59→### Decision 1: Static Analysis via Configurable Analyzer (Not Custom AST)\n    60→\n    61→**Decision:** Use Semgrep with custom YAML rules. Do NOT build a custom AST scanner.\n    62→\n    63→**Rationale (from research):**\n    64→- Semgrep's `pattern-not-inside` detects the absence of logging — exactly what we need\n    65→- YAML rules are editable project files — users customize for their logging library\n    66→- 30+ language support — works for TypeScript, Python, and future stacks\n    67→- 10-second median CI scan — fast enough for code review integration\n    68→- Building a custom AST scanner is high effort, single-language, and we'd be reinventing what Semgrep does\n    69→\n    70→**Interface:**\n    71→\n    72→```typescript\n    73→interface AnalyzerResult {\n    74→  tool: string;  // 'semgrep' | 'eslint' | 'custom'\n    75→  gaps: ObservabilityGap[];\n    76→  summary: {\n    77→    totalFunctions: number;\n    78→    functionsWithLogs: number;\n    79→    errorHandlersWithoutLogs: number;\n    80→    coveragePercent: number;\n    81→    levelDistribution: Record<string, number>;\n    82→  };\n    83→}\n    84→\n    85→interface ObservabilityGap {\n    86→  file: string;\n    87→  line: number;\n    88→  type: string;  // rule ID from analyzer\n    89→  description: string;\n    90→  severity: 'error' | 'warning' | 'info';\n    91→}\n    92→```\n    93→\n    94→**The harness defines the gap report format. Any tool that produces this format works.** Default: Semgrep. Users can configure ESLint, SonarQube, or custom tools.\n    95→\n    96→**Rule storage:** `patches/observability/*.yaml` — Semgrep rule files. Shipped with defaults, users customize per project.\n    97→\n    98→### Decision 2: Separate Metrics, Not Combined\n    99→\n   100→**Decision:** Report static coverage and runtime coverage as separate numbers. No weighted combination."}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01Du6Dm3wXgPT4dCoQ6SefyL","session_id":"e8d3a9d7-303a-4d24-9a07-31410ec54173","uuid":"7f9b198c-5dc3-4ab5-9f66-9f7f238f3da3","timestamp":"2026-03-23T15:13:28.719Z"}
