{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01WhKZvqNYzE6EwBB7T2mdaS","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→# Story 9-4: Multi-stage Dockerfile generation\n     2→\n     3→## Status: backlog\n     4→\n     5→## Story\n     6→\n     7→As a developer deploying a multi-stack project,\n     8→I want a single Dockerfile with build stages for each stack,\n     9→So that all components are built and packaged together.\n    10→\n    11→## Acceptance Criteria\n    12→\n    13→- [ ] AC1: Given a multi-stack project (nodejs + rust), when `generateDockerfileTemplate()` is called, then it produces a multi-stage Dockerfile with `node:22-slim` AND `rust:1.82-slim` build stages and a combined `debian:bookworm-slim` runtime stage <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n    14→- [ ] AC2: Given a single-stack project, when `generateDockerfileTemplate()` is called, then output is identical to the current single-stack template (no regression) <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n    15→- [ ] AC3: Given a multi-stack Dockerfile, when inspected, then each build stage is named `build-{stack}` and the runtime stage copies from all build stages <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n    16→\n    17→## Technical Notes\n    18→\n    19→### Changes to `src/modules/infra/dockerfile-template.ts`\n    20→\n    21→The current `generateDockerfileTemplate()` (L112) takes a single stack and produces a single-stack Dockerfile.\n    22→\n    23→**New function to add:**\n    24→```ts\n    25→export function generateMultiStackDockerfile(detections: StackDetection[]): string\n    26→```\n    27→\n    28→This function:\n    29→1. If `detections.length === 1`, delegate to existing single-stack template functions (`nodejsTemplate()`, `pythonTemplate()`, `rustTemplate()`) — output must be identical to current behavior.\n    30→2. If `detections.length > 1`, compose a multi-stage Dockerfile:\n    31→\n    32→**Multi-stage structure:**\n    33→```dockerfile\n    34→# Build stage for nodejs\n    35→FROM node:22-slim AS build-nodejs\n    36→WORKDIR /app/{dir}\n    37→COPY {dir}/package*.json ./\n    38→RUN npm ci\n    39→COPY {dir}/ ./\n    40→RUN npm run build\n    41→\n    42→# Build stage for rust\n    43→FROM rust:1.82-slim AS build-rust\n    44→WORKDIR /app/{dir}\n    45→COPY {dir}/Cargo.toml {dir}/Cargo.lock ./\n    46→RUN cargo build --release\n    47→\n    48→# Runtime\n    49→FROM debian:bookworm-slim\n    50→WORKDIR /app\n    51→COPY --from=build-nodejs /app/{dir}/dist ./frontend/dist\n    52→COPY --from=build-rust /app/{dir}/target/release/{binary} ./backend/\n    53→```\n    54→\n    55→Each `{dir}` comes from `StackDetection.dir`. Build stages are named `build-{stack}` (e.g., `build-nodejs`, `build-rust`).\n    56→\n    57→**Update existing function:**\n    58→Modify `generateDockerfileTemplate()` to accept `StackDetection[]` and delegate:\n    59→- Single detection → existing per-stack template (no regression)\n    60→- Multiple detections → `generateMultiStackDockerfile()`\n    61→\n    62→**Reuse existing templates as building blocks.** The existing `nodejsTemplate()`, `pythonTemplate()`, `rustTemplate()` functions produce complete Dockerfiles. Extract the build-stage portions from each to compose multi-stage builds. The runtime stage is new — it uses `debian:bookworm-slim` and copies artifacts from all build stages.\n    63→\n    64→### Import changes\n    65→\n    66→Import `StackDetection` from `../../lib/stack-detect`.\n    67→\n    68→### Test file\n    69→\n    70→Create/update `src/modules/infra/__tests__/dockerfile-template.test.ts`:\n    71→- Single-stack: output identical to current (snapshot or string comparison)\n    72→- Multi-stack (nodejs + rust): verify both `FROM` lines present, both `AS build-*` stages, combined runtime stage with `COPY --from` for each\n    73→- Multi-stack (nodejs + python): same pattern\n    74→- Verify `dir` values are used correctly in WORKDIR and COPY paths\n    75→\n    76→## Files to Change\n    77→\n    78→- `src/modules/infra/dockerfile-template.ts` — Add `generateMultiStackDockerfile(detections: StackDetection[])`, update `generateDockerfileTemplate()` to accept `StackDetection[]` and delegate, extract build-stage portions from existing per-stack templates\n    79→- `src/modules/infra/__tests__/dockerfile-template.test.ts` — Add multi-stage Dockerfile tests (multi-stack output, single-stack no-regression, stage naming, COPY --from verification)\n    80→"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01Du6Dm3wXgPT4dCoQ6SefyL","session_id":"e8d3a9d7-303a-4d24-9a07-31410ec54173","uuid":"f386fce2-41a9-4cdb-a716-a2a79b4e42b0","timestamp":"2026-03-23T15:15:24.124Z"}
