{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_012iG7i69CgRNFA5cXdkhMYD","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→<workflow>\n     2→  <critical>The workflow execution engine is governed by: {project-root}/_bmad/core/tasks/workflow.xml</critical>\n     3→  <critical>You MUST have already loaded and processed: {installed_path}/workflow.yaml</critical>\n     4→  <critical>Communicate all responses in {communication_language} and language MUST be tailored to {user_skill_level}</critical>\n     5→  <critical>Generate all documents in {document_output_language}</critical>\n     6→  <critical>Only modify the story file in these areas: Tasks/Subtasks checkboxes, Dev Agent Record (Debug Log, Completion Notes), File List,\n     7→    Change Log, and Status</critical>\n     8→  <critical>Execute ALL steps in exact order; do NOT skip steps</critical>\n     9→  <critical>Absolutely DO NOT stop because of \"milestones\", \"significant progress\", or \"session boundaries\". Continue in a single execution\n    10→    until the story is COMPLETE (all ACs satisfied and all tasks/subtasks checked) UNLESS a HALT condition is triggered or the USER gives\n    11→    other instruction.</critical>\n    12→  <critical>Do NOT schedule a \"next session\" or request review pauses unless a HALT condition applies. Only Step 6 decides completion.</critical>\n    13→  <critical>User skill level ({user_skill_level}) affects conversation style ONLY, not code updates.</critical>\n    14→\n    15→  <step n=\"1\" goal=\"Find next ready story and load it\" tag=\"sprint-status\">\n    16→    <check if=\"{{story_path}} is provided\">\n    17→      <action>Use {{story_path}} directly</action>\n    18→      <action>Read COMPLETE story file</action>\n    19→      <action>Extract story_key from filename or metadata</action>\n    20→      <goto anchor=\"task_check\" />\n    21→    </check>\n    22→\n    23→    <!-- Sprint-based story discovery -->\n    24→    <check if=\"{{sprint_status}} file exists\">\n    25→      <critical>MUST read COMPLETE sprint-status.yaml file from start to end to preserve order</critical>\n    26→      <action>Load the FULL file: {{sprint_status}}</action>\n    27→      <action>Read ALL lines from beginning to end - do not skip any content</action>\n    28→      <action>Parse the development_status section completely to understand story order</action>\n    29→\n    30→      <action>Find the FIRST story (by reading in order from top to bottom) where:\n    31→        - Key matches pattern: number-number-name (e.g., \"1-2-user-auth\")\n    32→        - NOT an epic key (epic-X) or retrospective (epic-X-retrospective)\n    33→        - Status value equals \"ready-for-dev\"\n    34→      </action>\n    35→\n    36→      <check if=\"no ready-for-dev or in-progress story found\">\n    37→        <output>📋 No ready-for-dev stories found in sprint-status.yaml\n    38→\n    39→          **Current Sprint Status:** {{sprint_status_summary}}\n    40→\n    41→          **What would you like to do?**\n    42→          1. Run `create-story` to create next story from epics with comprehensive context\n    43→          2. Run `*validate-create-story` to improve existing stories before development (recommended quality check)\n    44→          3. Specify a particular story file to develop (provide full path)\n    45→          4. Check {{sprint_status}} file to see current sprint status\n    46→\n    47→          💡 **Tip:** Stories in `ready-for-dev` may not have been validated. Consider running `validate-create-story` first for a quality\n    48→          check.\n    49→        </output>\n    50→        <ask>Choose option [1], [2], [3], or [4], or specify story file path:</ask>\n    51→\n    52→        <check if=\"user chooses '1'\">\n    53→          <action>HALT - Run create-story to create next story</action>\n    54→        </check>\n    55→\n    56→        <check if=\"user chooses '2'\">\n    57→          <action>HALT - Run validate-create-story to improve existing stories</action>\n    58→        </check>\n    59→\n    60→        <check if=\"user chooses '3'\">\n    61→          <ask>Provide the story file path to develop:</ask>\n    62→          <action>Store user-provided story path as {{story_path}}</action>\n    63→          <goto anchor=\"task_check\" />\n    64→        </check>\n    65→\n    66→        <check if=\"user chooses '4'\">\n    67→          <output>Loading {{sprint_status}} for detailed status review...</output>\n    68→          <action>Display detailed sprint status analysis</action>\n    69→          <action>HALT - User can review sprint status and provide story path</action>\n    70→        </check>\n    71→\n    72→        <check if=\"user provides story file path\">\n    73→          <action>Store user-provided story path as {{story_path}}</action>\n    74→          <goto anchor=\"task_check\" />\n    75→        </check>\n    76→      </check>\n    77→    </check>\n    78→\n    79→    <!-- Non-sprint story discovery -->\n    80→    <check if=\"{{sprint_status}} file does NOT exist\">\n    81→      <action>Search {implementation_artifacts} for stories directly</action>\n    82→      <action>Find stories with \"ready-for-dev\" status in files</action>\n    83→      <action>Look for story files matching pattern: *-*-*.md</action>\n    84→      <action>Read each candidate story file to check Status section</action>\n    85→\n    86→      <check if=\"no ready-for-dev stories found in story files\">\n    87→        <output>📋 No ready-for-dev stories found\n    88→\n    89→          **Available Options:**\n    90→          1. Run `create-story` to create next story from epics with comprehensive context\n    91→          2. Run `*validate-create-story` to improve existing stories\n    92→          3. Specify which story to develop\n    93→        </output>\n    94→        <ask>What would you like to do? Choose option [1], [2], or [3]:</ask>\n    95→\n    96→        <check if=\"user chooses '1'\">\n    97→          <action>HALT - Run create-story to create next story</action>\n    98→        </check>\n    99→\n   100→        <check if=\"user chooses '2'\">\n   101→          <action>HALT - Run validate-create-story to improve existing stories</action>\n   102→        </check>\n   103→\n   104→        <check if=\"user chooses '3'\">\n   105→          <ask>It's unclear what story you want developed. Please provide the full path to the story file:</ask>\n   106→          <action>Store user-provided story path as {{story_path}}</action>\n   107→          <action>Continue with provided story file</action>\n   108→        </check>\n   109→      </check>\n   110→\n   111→      <check if=\"ready-for-dev story found in files\">\n   112→        <action>Use discovered story file and extract story_key</action>\n   113→      </check>\n   114→    </check>\n   115→\n   116→    <action>Store the found story_key (e.g., \"1-2-user-authentication\") for later status updates</action>\n   117→    <action>Find matching story file in {implementation_artifacts} using story_key pattern: {{story_key}}.md</action>\n   118→    <action>Read COMPLETE story file from discovered path</action>\n   119→\n   120→    <anchor id=\"task_check\" />\n   121→\n   122→    <action>Parse sections: Story, Acceptance Criteria, Tasks/Subtasks, Dev Notes, Dev Agent Record, File List, Change Log, Status</action>\n   123→\n   124→    <action>Load comprehensive context from story file's Dev Notes section</action>\n   125→    <action>Extract developer guidance from Dev Notes: architecture requirements, previous learnings, technical specifications</action>\n   126→    <action>Use enhanced story context to inform implementation decisions and approaches</action>\n   127→\n   128→    <action>Identify first incomplete task (unchecked [ ]) in Tasks/Subtasks</action>\n   129→\n   130→    <action if=\"no incomplete tasks\">\n   131→      <goto step=\"6\">Completion sequence</goto>\n   132→    </action>\n   133→    <action if=\"story file inaccessible\">HALT: \"Cannot develop story without access to story file\"</action>\n   134→    <action if=\"incomplete task or subtask requirements ambiguous\">ASK user to clarify or HALT</action>\n   135→  </step>\n   136→\n   137→  <step n=\"2\" goal=\"Load project context and story information\">\n   138→    <critical>Load all available context to inform implementation</critical>\n   139→\n   140→    <action>Load {project_context} for coding standards and project-wide patterns (if exists)</action>\n   141→    <action>Parse sections: Story, Acceptance Criteria, Tasks/Subtasks, Dev Notes, Dev Agent Record, File List, Change Log, Status</action>\n   142→    <action>Load comprehensive context from story file's Dev Notes section</action>\n   143→    <action>Extract developer guidance from Dev Notes: architecture requirements, previous learnings, technical specifications</action>\n   144→    <action>Use enhanced story context to inform implementation decisions and approaches</action>\n   145→    <output>✅ **Context Loaded**\n   146→      Story and project context available for implementation\n   147→    </output>\n   148→  </step>\n   149→\n   150→  <step n=\"3\" goal=\"Detect review continuation and extract review context\">\n   151→    <critical>Determine if this is a fresh start or continuation after code review</critical>\n   152→\n   153→    <action>Check if \"Senior Developer Review (AI)\" section exists in the story file</action>\n   154→    <action>Check if \"Review Follow-ups (AI)\" subsection exists under Tasks/Subtasks</action>\n   155→\n   156→    <check if=\"Senior Developer Review section exists\">\n   157→      <action>Set review_continuation = true</action>\n   158→      <action>Extract from \"Senior Developer Review (AI)\" section:\n   159→        - Review outcome (Approve/Changes Requested/Blocked)\n   160→        - Review date\n   161→        - Total action items with checkboxes (count checked vs unchecked)\n   162→        - Severity breakdown (High/Med/Low counts)\n   163→      </action>\n   164→      <action>Count unchecked [ ] review follow-up tasks in \"Review Follow-ups (AI)\" subsection</action>\n   165→      <action>Store list of unchecked review items as {{pending_review_items}}</action>\n   166→\n   167→      <output>⏯️ **Resuming Story After Code Review** ({{review_date}})\n   168→\n   169→        **Review Outcome:** {{review_outcome}}\n   170→        **Action Items:** {{unchecked_review_count}} remaining to address\n   171→        **Priorities:** {{high_count}} High, {{med_count}} Medium, {{low_count}} Low\n   172→\n   173→        **Strategy:** Will prioritize review follow-up tasks (marked [AI-Review]) before continuing with regular tasks.\n   174→      </output>\n   175→    </check>\n   176→\n   177→    <check if=\"Senior Developer Review section does NOT exist\">\n   178→      <action>Set review_continuation = false</action>\n   179→      <action>Set {{pending_review_items}} = empty</action>\n   180→\n   181→      <output>🚀 **Starting Fresh Implementation**\n   182→\n   183→        Story: {{story_key}}\n   184→        Story Status: {{current_status}}\n   185→        First incomplete task: {{first_task_description}}\n   186→      </output>\n   187→    </check>\n   188→  </step>\n   189→\n   190→  <step n=\"4\" goal=\"Mark story in-progress\" tag=\"sprint-status\">\n   191→    <check if=\"{{sprint_status}} file exists\">\n   192→      <action>Load the FULL file: {{sprint_status}}</action>\n   193→      <action>Read all development_status entries to find {{story_key}}</action>\n   194→      <action>Get current status value for development_status[{{story_key}}]</action>\n   195→\n   196→      <check if=\"current status == 'ready-for-dev' OR review_continuation == true\">\n   197→        <action>Update the story in the sprint status report to = \"in-progress\"</action>\n   198→        <output>🚀 Starting work on story {{story_key}}\n   199→          Status updated: ready-for-dev → in-progress\n   200→        </output>\n   201→      </check>\n   202→\n   203→      <check if=\"current status == 'in-progress'\">\n   204→        <output>⏯️ Resuming work on story {{story_key}}\n   205→          Story is already marked in-progress\n   206→        </output>\n   207→      </check>\n   208→\n   209→      <check if=\"current status is neither ready-for-dev nor in-progress\">\n   210→        <output>⚠️ Unexpected story status: {{current_status}}\n   211→          Expected ready-for-dev or in-progress. Continuing anyway...\n   212→        </output>\n   213→      </check>\n   214→\n   215→      <action>Store {{current_sprint_status}} for later use</action>\n   216→    </check>\n   217→\n   218→    <check if=\"{{sprint_status}} file does NOT exist\">\n   219→      <output>ℹ️ No sprint status file exists - story progress will be tracked in story file only</output>\n   220→      <action>Set {{current_sprint_status}} = \"no-sprint-tracking\"</action>\n   221→    </check>\n   222→  </step>\n   223→\n   224→  <step n=\"5\" goal=\"Implement task following red-green-refactor cycle\">\n   225→    <critical>FOLLOW THE STORY FILE TASKS/SUBTASKS SEQUENCE EXACTLY AS WRITTEN - NO DEVIATION</critical>\n   226→\n   227→    <action>Review the current task/subtask from the story file - this is your authoritative implementation guide</action>\n   228→    <action>Plan implementation following red-green-refactor cycle</action>\n   229→\n   230→    <!-- RED PHASE -->\n   231→    <action>Write FAILING tests first for the task/subtask functionality</action>\n   232→    <action>Confirm tests fail before implementation - this validates test correctness</action>\n   233→\n   234→    <!-- GREEN PHASE -->\n   235→    <action>Implement MINIMAL code to make tests pass</action>\n   236→    <action>Run tests to confirm they now pass</action>\n   237→    <action>Handle error conditions and edge cases as specified in task/subtask</action>\n   238→\n   239→    <!-- REFACTOR P