{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01V7JqrarmvwTmGzFDAZKSv1","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→# Showboat Proof: 8-5 Rust Dockerfile Template Generation\n     2→\n     3→## Test Environment\n     4→\n     5→- **Type:** Local development (macOS)\n     6→- **Date:** 2026-03-23\n     7→- **Tool:** Vitest unit tests + codeharness coverage\n     8→- **Story:** 8-5-rust-dockerfile-template\n     9→\n    10→## AC #1: generateDockerfileTemplate returns ok with stack: 'rust'\n    11→\n    12→**Test:** `returns stack: rust and correct path`\n    13→**Evidence:** `generateDockerfileTemplate('/project', 'rust')` returns `{ success: true, data: { path: '/project/Dockerfile', stack: 'rust' } }` — NOT `'generic'`.\n    14→\n    15→**Verdict:** PASS\n    16→\n    17→## AC #2: Multi-stage build with correct FROM lines\n    18→\n    19→**Test:** `contains FROM rust:1.82-slim AS builder and FROM debian:bookworm-slim`\n    20→**Evidence:** Written content contains both `FROM rust:1.82-slim AS builder` (builder stage) and `FROM debian:bookworm-slim` (runtime stage).\n    21→\n    22→**Verdict:** PASS\n    23→\n    24→## AC #3: cargo build --release and COPY --from=builder\n    25→\n    26→**Tests:** `includes cargo build --release in builder stage`, `includes COPY --from=builder to copy compiled binary`\n    27→**Evidence:** Written content contains `cargo build --release` in builder stage and `COPY --from=builder /build/target/release/myapp /usr/local/bin/myapp` in runtime stage.\n    28→\n    29→**Verdict:** PASS\n    30→"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_017jkzWrDhmfYHNpbYuB4NZk","session_id":"e8d3a9d7-303a-4d24-9a07-31410ec54173","uuid":"06f26ef5-fc84-4cfb-b3e6-ba1438b12579","timestamp":"2026-03-23T15:24:13.954Z"}
