{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_01ALuaGkamBaxZVuVjTCEseq","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01QBrxSNdbjhmJHFkiUGbWGT","name":"Bash","input":{"command":"STORY_CONTENT=$(cat /tmp/codeharness-verify-9-4-multi-stage-dockerfile-generation/story.md)\nCONTAINER=\"codeharness-verify\"\nSTORY_KEY=\"9-4-multi-stage-dockerfile-generation\"\n\n# Build the verification prompt\nPROMPT=\"You are a black-box verifier. Your job is to verify that a software feature works correctly from the user's perspective — using ONLY the installed CLI, documentation, and observability data. You have NO access to source code.\n\n## Why Black-Box Verification\n\nThis workspace contains NO source code. The src/ directory does not exist. This is intentional — you must verify the feature works as a user would experience it, not by reading implementation details.\n\n## Step 1: Read README.md\n\nStart by reading README.md in this workspace.\n\n## Step 2: Review Acceptance Criteria\n\nThe story file story.md contains the acceptance criteria you must verify. Here is its content:\n\n---\n${STORY_CONTENT}\n---\n\n## Step 3: Verify Each AC\n\nFor EACH acceptance criterion:\n1. Run commands inside the Docker container via docker exec ${CONTAINER} ...\n2. Capture the command output as evidence\n3. Query observability endpoints if runtime evidence is needed\n\n### Docker Container\n- Container name: ${CONTAINER}\n- ALL CLI commands MUST run via: docker exec ${CONTAINER} <command>\n- Example: docker exec ${CONTAINER} codeharness --version\n\nThe container has: codeharness, claude, curl, jq, showboat, node, npm\n\n### Project Type: Node.js CLI\n\nExecute commands inside the container and capture stdout/stderr as evidence:\n- docker exec ${CONTAINER} <cli-command> [args]\n- Capture exit codes: docker exec ${CONTAINER} sh -c '<command>; echo EXIT:\\$?'\n- For Node.js projects, the built artifact is installed globally in the container.\n\n### Observability Endpoints\n\nQuery these from the HOST for runtime evidence:\n- VictoriaLogs: http://localhost:9428\n- VictoriaMetrics: http://localhost:8428\n- VictoriaTraces: http://localhost:16686\n\n## Step 4: Write Proof Document\n\nWrite your verification proof to: verification/${STORY_KEY}-proof.md\n\nUse this format for each AC:\n\\`\\`\\`markdown\n## AC N: <description>\n\\`\\`\\`bash\ndocker exec ${CONTAINER} <command>\n\\`\\`\\`\n\\`\\`\\`output\n<actual output>\n\\`\\`\\`\n\\`\\`\\`\n\nIMPORTANT: Only use bash and output as code fence languages.\n\n## Critical Rules\n\n1. ALL commands MUST use docker exec ${CONTAINER} ... — do NOT run commands directly on the host.\n2. Do NOT attempt to access source code — there is no src/ directory.\n3. Report REAL failures — do NOT fabricate passing evidence.\n4. Every AC needs functional evidence — reading docs alone is not evidence.\n5. Verify aggressively, escalate narrowly.\n6. ESCALATE is ONLY for things genuinely impossible to automate.\n7. Never switch to unit-testable verification.\"\n\ncd /tmp/codeharness-verify-${STORY_KEY} && claude --print --max-budget-usd 5 --allowedTools Bash Read Write Glob Grep Edit -p \"${PROMPT}\" 2>&1","description":"Run verifier session for story 9-4","timeout":300000},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":5995,"cache_read_input_tokens":53627,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":5995},"output_tokens":8,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"e8d3a9d7-303a-4d24-9a07-31410ec54173","uuid":"14156b42-a5db-46ae-b9b7-f9d272315b1f"}
